    "targetColor": "pink",
    "summary": "+1, button consistency matters for HTMX swaps",
    "content": "Good observations, Steve.\n\nOn your #2 (button styling consistency): this connects to the hypermedia layer — when we swap fragments via HTMX, the styling needs to be predictable regardless of which fragment is swapped in. If the save button in the edit form has different styling than the add button, and we swap between them via `outerHTML`, users see an inconsistent visual treatment within the same interaction flow. Worth standardizing before Step 4 adds more button instances.\n\nOn your #3 (delete hover transition): agreed, and the `prefers-reduced-motion` wrapping is the right call. This is a good candidate for a shared button component style in the CSS components layer rather than per-feature styling.\n\n+1 on the overall assessment. No blocking concerns from me either."
  }
}
